articles.author: Jan Lopatka, David W. Cerny
articles.description: Slovaks were voting on Saturday in a parliamentary election closely fought between former leftist Prime Minister Robert Fico, who wants to end military aid for neighbouring Ukraine, and pro-Western liberals.
articles.title: Slovaks choose between pro-Russian ex-PM Fico and pro-Western liberals

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Italy's coast guard rescued 177 people including 27 crew from a ferry that caught fire travelling from the Italian island of Lampedusa to Porto Empedocle in Sicily, it said on Saturday.
articles.title: Italy's coast guard rescues 177 people aboard burning ferry

articles.author: Steve Scherer
articles.description: Canadian Sikhs are grateful to Prime Minister Justin Trudeau for giving voice to their fears and standing up to India at the risk of severe backlash from New Delhi, which he said could be linked to the murder of a Sikh separatist leader.
articles.title: Canada's Sikhs are grateful - and afraid - after Trudeau's India allegations

articles.author: Miguel Pereira, Catarina Demony
articles.description: Marcia Leandro moved to Portugal from Brazil six months ago with a goal: to train as a chef. But Portugal's housing crisis curbed her dreams and forced her to live in a tent.
articles.title: Tent-dwelling migrants join protest over Portugal's housing prices

articles.author: Saleem Ahmed
articles.description: The death toll from a large blast at a mosque in Pakistan rose to 59 on Saturday as the government vowed to find the perpetrators and accused India's intelligence agency of being involved.
articles.title: Death toll from Pakistan blast rises to 59 as minister blames India

articles.author: Mohamed Junayd
articles.description: Opposition candidate Mohamed Muizzu is projected to win the Maldives presidential run-off vote on Saturday, beating incumbent Ibrahim Solih, local media said, in a result that could see the Indian Ocean archipelago shift closer to China.
articles.title: Opposition candidate Muizzu projected to win Maldives presidency, local media report

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Senegalese Navy said it had intercepted two wooden boats carrying 272 would-be migrants 100 km (60 miles) off the coast of the capital Dakar on Friday.
articles.title: Senegalese navy stops two migrant boats carrying 272 people

articles.author: Andy Sullivan, David Morgan
articles.description: Lawmakers return to Congress on Saturday with no clear path to resolving a squabble that appears likely to close wide swaths of the federal government, from national parks to financial regulation, in less than 18 hours.
articles.title: Congress tees up votes in last-minute scramble to avert shutdown

articles.author: Dave Sherwood
articles.description: Cuban seamstress Yamidely Cervantes has bought a new sewing machine for the first time in years, plus a refrigerator and a cellphone - all on Russia's dime.
articles.title: How Cubans were recruited to fight for Russia

articles.author: Lisa Richwine, Steve Gorman
articles.description: An admitted former street gang leader was arrested on Friday on a charge of murder in the Las Vegas shooting death of hip-hop star Tupac Shakur nearly three decades ago, a long-unsolved crime that became a defining moment in the history of rap music.
articles.title: Suspect in rapper Tupac Shakur's 1996 slaying charged with murder in Las Vegas
